==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Breechblock
<hw>Breech"block</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The movable
piece which closes the breech of a breech-loading firearm, and resists
the backward force of the discharge. It is withdrawn for the insertion
of a cartridge, and closed again before the gun is fired.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Breechcloth</ent>⟦br⟧
